subject: RE: Minnesota Council on Foundations - RUBI RFP File Path, Assignments, & Questions
body:
Hi Hannah,
 
Nassise, Dan, and I had some time to chat about our 2 combined requests (number 2 and 7). Our insights are in the Word doc here:
 
 
We do need to add in a question for Paul about what he means by Community Member. Does that mean people in MCF, Affiliate Company Leaders, Affiliate Company teammates, or just people who live in Minnesota from either a Rural/Urban area…
 
Please, let me know if you have any questions or concerns.
 
Thank you,
 
CW
 
From:
 Hannah Strack <h.strack@lcwmail.com> 
Sent:
 Tuesday, June 13, 2023 9:56 AM
To:
 Nassise Geleta <n.geleta@lcwmail.com>; Conner Williams <c.williams@lcwmail.com>; Daniel Gough <d.gough@lcwmail.com>; Grace Vottero <g.vottero@lcwmail.com>
Cc:
 Melissa Neu <m.neu@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Minnesota Council on Foundations - RUBI RFP File Path, Assignments, & Questions
 
Hello Everyone, 
 
Thanks for your help in working to get this new proposal out for the RUBI RFP out with such a short timeline! As a reminder, 
all drafts of this proposal are due EOD, Wednesday, June 14
th
 with the 
final submission deadline being Friday, June 16
th
 EOB.
  When your draft is completed, please send it to me and I’ll update it on the new Word Doc. 
 
All documents for the RUBI MCF RFP will still be in the 
Minnesota Council on Foundations file in Dropbox
 
but there is a separate file titled RUBI – Minnesota Council on Foundations
 where all work will be stored. The pathway is shown here: 
 
Each of the assignments for the proposal submission are listed below:
 
Proposal Submission & Eval Assignments
1. Melissa & Hannah
2. Dan, Conner, & Nassise
3. Dan
4. Grace
5. Melissa & Hannah
6. Melissa & Hannah
7. Dan, Conner, & Nassise
8. Melissa & Hannah 
 
In preparation for the call with Paul Masiarchin, the questions we spoke about at the meeting are listed here: 
 
Questions:
 
How will MCF partner with LCW regarding “collecting input from community members”, found in the Purpose of Request section, for the urban and rural populations? Will MCF be drawing on their networks?
Are there any conditions that would preclude LCW from future RFP’s?
 
Please let me know if I’ve missed anything or if you hit any snags in the process and thanks again!
 
Best,
Hannah

subject: Get In Front Of More Buyers. Pre-Register with Our Partners!
body:
Want to attract more business and get in front of more buyers? Learn how.
 
Supplier Newsletter 
June 2023
Register with Our Partners!
Take advantage of our strategic partnerships.
We have great partnerships with great companies, and they're looking for suppliers like you!
SupplierGATEWAY wants to help small and diverse suppliers like you access more opportunities to work with some of the World's most recognized brands.
Are you a supplier in one of the following industries, or do you want to be?
Healthcare
Construction/Infrastructure
Commercial Real Estate
eCommerce
Sports and Entertainment
Small Business
 You can register with multiple partners as well, so there's no need to pick and choose.  
Commercial Real Estate Diverse Supplier
(CREDS) Consortium
 
 
How To Access Capital For Small Business Owners: A Step-By-Step Guide
Accessing capital as a small business can be tough and confusing. 
 
In this article, we cover the different types of funding available for start-up businesses and provide some tips on where and how to get started in applying for these funds. 
Read More on The Blog
 
 
SupplierGATEWAY is excited to be providing supplier management software solutions for Xylem, CHOC Children's, and Unibail-Rodamco-Westfield among several other new clients! 
 
If you're a supplier in industrial, medical, or commercial real estate industries  head to their portals by clicking on their logos and pre-register!
 
Xylem is a global water technology provider helping our customers solve the world's toughest water challenges across utility, industrial, commercial, and residential markets worldwide.
 
Children’s Hospital of Orange County (CHOC), a pediatric healthcare system based in Orange County, California, is committed to being a leading destination for children’s health by providing exceptional and innovative care. CHOC’s growing community includes two state-of-the-art hospitals in Orange and Mission Viejo and a regional network of primary and specialty care clinics serving children and families in four counties.
 
Unibail-Rodamco-Westield is the creator and operator of unique, sustainability-driven retail, office and lifestyle destinations that connect people through extraordinary, meaningful shared experiences.
